params.text:
Add exception values

An exception has a tag and a payload. Throw instruction supports
throwing arbitrary values, but creating proper exceptions should be
available to user code.

Example - create an exception with payload:

    .name: iota tag
    .name: iota value
    .name: iota ex

    atom %tag local 'Some_error'
    exception %ex local %tag local %value local
    throw %ex local

Example - create an exception without payload:

    .name: iota tag
    .name: iota ex

    atom %tag local 'Some_error'
    exception %ex local %tag local void
    throw %ex local
